{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TXFpYPDEueJRy8qnSxrimW","type":"tool_result","content":"100\t/** Default maximum loop iterations before termination. */\n101\tconst DEFAULT_MAX_ITERATIONS = 5;\n102\t\n103\t// --- Crash Recovery: Task Completion Check ---\n104\t\n105\t/**\n106\t * Check whether a (taskName, storyKey) combination is already recorded\n107\t * in the workflow state's tasks_completed array.\n108\t *\n109\t * Both fields must match for the task to be considered completed.\n110\t * Used by the resume logic to skip already-completed dispatches.\n111\t */\n112\texport function isTaskCompleted(\n113\t  state: WorkflowState,\n114\t  taskName: string,\n115\t  storyKey: string,\n116\t): boolean {\n117\t  return state.tasks_completed.some(\n118\t    (cp) => cp.task_name === taskName && cp.story_key === storyKey && !cp.error,\n119\t  );\n120\t}\n121\t\n122\t/**\n123\t * Check whether a (taskName, storyKey) combination has been completed\n124\t * enough times to cover the current iteration in a loop block.\n125\t *\n126\t * Loop tasks execute the same (taskName, storyKey) pair each iteration,\n127\t * recording a new checkpoint each time. To determine if a task is done\n128\t * for the current iteration, we count how many matching checkpoints exist\n129\t * and compare to the current iteration number.\n130\t */\n131\texport function isLoopTaskCompleted(\n132\t  state: WorkflowState,\n133\t  taskName: string,\n134\t  storyKey: string,\n135\t  iteration: number,\n136\t): boolean {\n137\t  const count = state.tasks_completed.filter(\n138\t    (cp) => cp.task_name === taskName && cp.story_key === storyKey && !cp.error,\n139\t  ).length;\n140\t  return count >= iteration;\n141\t}\n142\t\n143\t// --- Work Item Loading ---\n144\t\n145\t/**\n146\t * Load work items from sprint-status.yaml and optionally issues.yaml.\n147\t *\n148\t * Stories are extracted from the `development_status` section of sprint-status.yaml.\n149\t * Issues 