{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017cqb76qurL8ij6LsD8qadk","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**Summary of changes:**\n\n**`src/lib/workflow-engine.ts`** — Added `propagateVerifyFlags()` private function that reads harness state via `readStateWithBody()`, conditionally sets `session_flags.tests_passed` (when `failed === 0`) and `session_flags.coverage_met` (when `coverage >= target`), and writes state back in a single I/O operation. The function is called after all 6 `dispatchTaskWithResult` call sites. Guards ensure it only runs for `taskName === 'implement'` with non-null `testResults`.\n\n**`src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts`** — Added mocks for `readStateWithBody` and `writeState` from `state.js`. Added 8 unit tests covering all 8 acceptance criteria: tests_passed set on `failed === 0`, coverage_met set when coverage meets target, no propagation for null testResults, no propagation for non-implement tasks, failed > 0 does not set tests_passed, coverage < target does not set coverage_met, null coverage does not set coverage_met, both flags set in single write, and graceful handling of state file errors.\n\nAll 4747 tests pass. Story marked as `review`.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Observation:** The engine currently hardcodes `testResults: null` in all output contracts it builds (lines 372 and 564 of workflow-engine.ts). Flag propagation will not activate in production until a future story adds test result parsing from agent output. The logic is correct and tested via contract mutation in the `writeOutputContract` mock — when `testResults` is populated, propagation works as specified.\n- **Workaround:** Tests use `writeOutputContract` mock interception to mutate the contract object in-place (casting past the `readonly` interface) to inject `testResults`. This works because the engine creates plain object literals that aren't frozen, but it's coupling to an implementation detail.\n- **Tech debt:** The `HarnessState` type import was added then removed (unused). The `readStateWithBody` function signature returns a mutable `HarnessState` despite the interface having no readonly modifiers — the flag mutation (`state.session_flags.tests_passed = true`) works but relies on this mutability.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 25\n- By tool: Bash: 5, Read: 13, Edit: 11, Grep: 7, Write: 0, other: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npx vitest run` full suite (~20 lines), `npx tsc --noEmit` (~30 lines), `npx vitest run workflow-engine.test.ts` (~15 lines)\n- Files read: 7 unique, 13 total reads\n  - `workflow-engine.ts` read 5 times (different offset ranges)\n  - `workflow-engine.test.ts` read 5 times (different offset ranges)\n  - `state.ts` read 2 times\n- Redundant operations: None significant. Multiple reads of the same files were necessary due to file size (workflow-engine.ts ~1300 lines, test file ~3600 lines) — different sections needed at different stages."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a21bb17e63d1899ee (use SendMessage with to: 'a21bb17e63d1899ee' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 61845\ntool_uses: 65\nduration_ms: 372848</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9476bbd2-ee0a-4a5e-ac2a-0ed5228c47bf","uuid":"e1141357-0dbd-430b-aff4-72c522d1375d","timestamp":"2026-04-03T18:12:58.829Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-4-verify-flag-propagation.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for review. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously through all tasks until complete. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (build failures, test failures, unclear task specs, missing APIs)\n- Workarounds applied (anything hacky, copied patterns that felt wrong, TO