{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BnSGw1fUXQxHPqHazoW12r","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 16.4: Verify Flag Propagation\n2\t\n3\tStatus: review\n4\t\n5\t## Story\n6\t\n7\tAs a developer,\n8\tI want the engine to set `tests_passed` and `coverage_met` from the dev task's output contract,\n9\tso that verification doesn't fail on missing flags set by subagents.\n10\t\n11\t## Acceptance Criteria\n12\t\n13\t1. **Given** the implement task completes with an output contract containing `testResults`, **when** `testResults.failed === 0`, **then** the engine sets `session_flags.tests_passed = true` in the harness state file (`.codeharness/state.yaml`). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n14\t\n15\t2. **Given** the implement task completes with an output contract containing `testResults`, **when** `testResults.coverage >= coverage.target` from the harness state, **then** the engine sets `session_flags.coverage_met = true` in the harness state file. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n16\t\n17\t3. **Given** the implement task completes with an output contract that has no `testResults` (null), **when** the engine processes the output contract, **then** neither `tests_passed` nor `coverage_met` is changed — existing behavior is preserved. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n18\t\n19\t4. **Given** the implement task completes with `testResults.failed > 0`, **when** the engine processes the output contract, **then** `tests_passed` remains `false` (the engine does NOT set it). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t5. **Given** the implement task completes with `testResults.coverage < coverage.target`, **when** the engine processes the output contract, **then** `coverage_met` remains `false`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n22\t\n23\t6. **Given** flag propagation runs after the implement task, **when** the verify task subsequently starts, **then** it reads `tests_passed = true` and `coverage_met = true` from state and its precondition check passes without re-running coverage. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t7. **Given** the engine's flag propagation logic, **when** the task name is NOT `implement` (e.g., `verify`, `telemetry`, `retry`), **then** no flag propagation occurs — only the implement task triggers flag writes. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n26\t\n27\t8. **Given** the output contract has `testResults.coverage = null`, **when** flag propagation runs, **then** `coverage_met` is not changed (null coverage is not >= any target). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n28\t\n29\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n30\t\n31\t- [x] Task 1: Add flag propagation logic to `workflow-engine.ts` (AC: #1, #2, #3, #4, #5, #7, #8)\n32\t  - [x] Import `readStateWithBody` and `writeState` from `../state.js` (harness state, not workflow state)\n33\t  - [x] After `dispatchTaskWithResult` completes for a task named `implement`, check if the returned output contract has `testResults`\n34\t  - [x] If `testResults.failed === 0`, read harness state, set `session_flags.tests_passed = true`, write state\n35\t  - [x] If `testResults.coverage !== null && testResults.coverage >= state.coverage.target`, set `session_flags.coverage_met = true`\n36\t  - [x] Write state once (read, set both flags, write) to avoid double I/O\n37\t  - [x] Guard: only run for `taskName === 'implement'` — skip for all other task names\n38\t  - [x] Guard: skip entirely if `outputContract?.testResults` is null/undefined\n39\t\n40\t- [x] Task 2: Extract flag propagation into a helper function (AC: #1-#8)\n41\t  - [x] Create `propagateVerifyFlags(taskName: string, contract: OutputContract | null, projectDir: string): void`\n42\t  - [x] Function is pure side-effect (writes to state file) — returns void\n43\t  - [x] Keep it inside `workflow-engine.ts` as a private function (not exported) — it's engine-internal logic\n44\t  - [x] Call from both the sequential dispatch path and the loop block dispatch path\n45\t\n46\t- [x] Task 3: Write unit tests (AC: #1-#8)\n47\t  - [x] Test: implement task with `failed === 0` sets `tests_passed = true`\n48\t  - [x] Test: implement task with `coverage >= target` sets `coverage_met = true`\n49\t  - [x] Test: implement task with `failed > 0` does NOT set `tests_passed`\n50\t  - [x] Test: implement task with `coverage < target` does NOT set `coverage_met`\n51\t  - [x] Test: implement task with `testResults: null` does not change any flags\n52\t  - [x] Test: non-implement task (e.g., `verify`) does not trigger flag propagation\n53\t  - [x] Test: `testResults.coverage = null` does not set `coverage_met`\n54\t  - [x] Test: both flags set in single state write when both conditions met\n55\t\n56\t- [x] Task 4: Verify integration with existing verify module (AC: #6)\n57\t  - [x] Confirm `checkPreconditions()` in `src/modules/verify/orchestrator.ts` reads the flags that the engine now sets\n58\t  - [x] No changes needed to the verify module — it already reads `session_flags.tests_passed` and `session_flags.coverage_met`\n59\t\n60\t## Dev Notes\n61\t\n62\t### Architecture Constraints\n63\t\n64\t- **Modified file:** `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — add flag propagation after implement task dispatch.\n65\t- **Imported module:** `src/lib/state.ts` — the harness state module that manages `.codeharness/state.yaml`. Use `readStateWithBody()` and `writeState()`.\n66\t- **No new files.** The logic is engine-internal and belongs in `workflow-engine.ts`.\n67\t- **No new dependencies.** Only uses existing `state.ts` imports.\n68\t\n69\t### Architecture Decision Reference\n70\t\n71\tArchitecture Decision 7 (architecture-parallel-execution.md) specifies:\n72\t\n73\t```typescript\n74\t// After implement task completes:\n75\tif (taskName === 'implement' && outputContract?.testResults) {\n76\t  const { passed, failed, coverage } = outputContract.testResults;\n77\t  if (failed === 0) await setState('tests_passed', true);\n78\t  if (coverage >= state.coverage.target) await setState('coverage_met', true);\n79\t}\n80\t```\n81\t\n82\tThis pseudocode must be adapted to the actual API: `readStateWithBody()` returns `{ state, body }`, and `writeState(state, dir, body)` writes back.\n83\t\n84\t### Current Flag Setting Mechanism\n85\t\n86\tToday, `tests_passed` and `coverage_met` are set by `src/lib/coverage/evaluator.ts` (line 48-49) in `updateState()`:\n87\t```typescript\n88\tstate.session_flags.tests_passed = result.testsPassed;\n89\tstate.session_flags.coverage_met = evaluation.met;\n90\t```\n91\t\n92\tThis runs when coverage is explicitly evaluated. The problem: in the workflow engine flow, the implement task's output contract already contains test results, but the flags aren't set until the verify/coverage step runs. If the verify step can't set them (e.g., subagent context issues), verification fails.\n93\t\n94\tStory 16-4 adds a second path: the engine sets these flags immediately after the implement task, before verify runs. The coverage evaluator's path remains unchanged — it will overwrite with the same values or correct values if re-running coverage.\n95\t\n96\t### Integration Points\n97\t\n98\t1. **`dispatchTaskWithResult()`** — the function that runs a regular (non-null) task dispatch. After it returns, check the output contract.\n99\t2. **Loop block dispatch** — tasks inside `loop:` blocks also call `dispatchTaskWithResult()`. The implement task can appear inside a loop (retry pattern). Flag propagation must run after each dispatch in the loop too.\n100\t3. **`readStateWithBody()` / `writeState()`** — from `src/lib/state.ts`. The harness state file is at `{projectDir}/.codeharness/state.yaml`.\n101\t\n102\t### Where to Insert the Call\n103\t\n104\tThe engine has multiple dispatch call sites. The flag propagation helper should be called after every `dispatchTaskWithResult` return. Look for all call sites of `dispatchTaskWithResult` in the engine and insert the call after each one. The helper itself checks `taskName === 'implement'` so it's safe to call unconditionally.\n105\t\n106\tKey call sites in `workflow-engine.ts`:\n107\t- Sequential flow dispatch (~line 1215)\n108\t- Per-item flow dispatch (~line 1247)\n109\t- Loop block regular dispatch (~line 809)\n110\t- Loop block evaluator dispatch (~line 841) — this is for evaluator tasks, skip flag propagation (evaluators are not implement tasks)\n111\t\n112\t### Edge Cases\n113\t\n114\t- **`testResults.coverage` is `null`:** The dev agent may not report coverage. `null >= 80` is `false` in JS, so `coverage_met` won't be set. This is correct behavior.\n115\t- **Multiple implement dispatches (retry loop):** Each successful retry will re-set the flags. This is idempotent — setting `true` multiple times is fine.\n116\t- **`projectDir` resolution:** The engine's `EngineConfig` does not currently carry `projectDir`. Use `process.cwd()` or extract from the sprint status path. Check how the engine resolves the project directory.\n117\t\n118\t### Testing Strategy\n119\t\n120\t- Tests go in `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts` (existing test file).\n121\t- Mock `readStateWithBody` and `writeState` from `state.ts`.\n122\t- Create an output contract with various `testResults` configurations.\n123\t- Assert that state writes happen with correct flag values.\n124\t- Verify no state writes for non-implement tasks.\n125\t\n126\t### Project Structure Notes\n127\t\n128\t- Source: `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts`\n129\t- Tests: `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts`\n130\t- Build: TypeScript compiled to `dist/`\n131\t- Test runner: vitest\n132\t- ESM module — use `.js` extensions in imports\n133\t\n134\t### References\n135\t\n136\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-parallel-execution.md#Story 16.4]\n137\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Decision 7 — Verify Flag Propagation]\n138\t- [Source: src/lib/state.ts — readStateWithBody, writeState, HarnessState interface]\n139\t- [Source: src/lib/coverage/evaluator.ts — current flag setting mechanism (lines 48-49)]\n140\t- [Source: src/modules/verify/orchestrator.ts — checkPreconditions reads tests_passed/coverage_met]\n141\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/types.ts — OutputContract, TestResults interfaces]\n142\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-engine.ts — dispatchTaskWithResult, executeNullTask]\n143\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-3-telemetry-writer.md — previous story context]\n144\t\n145\t### Previous Story (16-3) Intelligence\n146\t\n147\t- Telemetry writer implemented successfully. `writeTelemetryEntry` registered as real handler in `null-task-registry.ts`.\n148\t- `TaskContext` includes `outputContract` — the output contract from the previous task. This is how data flows between tasks.\n149\t- All 4676+ tests pass. Do not break existing tests.\n150\t- Code review caught: duplicate type definitions, missing `projectDir` parameter, misleading JSDoc. Be precise in imports and types.\n151\t- Commit pattern: `feat: story 16-4 — verify flag propagation`\n152\t\n153\t### Git Intelligence\n154\t\n155\tRecent commits:\n156\t- `1831a88 feat: story 16-3 — telemetry writer module`\n157\t- `07e94a2 feat: story 16-2 — engine-handled null tasks`\n158\t- `e3c4761 feat: story 16-1 — hierarchical flow schema & parser`\n159\t- Pattern: feature commits use `feat: story {N}-{M} — {title}`\n160\t\n161\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n162\t## Verification Requirements\n163\t\n164\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/16-4-verify-flag-propagation-proof.md)\n165\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n166\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n167\t\n168\t## Documentation Requirements\n169\t\n170\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n171\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/16-4-verify-flag-propagation.md\n172\t\n173\t## Testing Requirements\n174\t\n175\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n176\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n177\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n178\t\n179\t## Dev Agent Record\n180\t\n181\t### Agent Model Used\n182\t\n183\tClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n184\t\n185\t### Debug Log References\n186\t\n187\tNone.\n188\t\n189\t### Completion Notes List\n190\t\n191\t- Added `propagateVerifyFlags()` private function to `workflow-engine.ts` — reads harness state, sets `tests_passed` and `coverage_met` flags, writes state back in a single I/O operation.\n192\t- Inserted `propagateVerifyFlags()` calls after all 6 `dispatchTaskWithResult` call sites (dispatchTask wrapper, loop per-story, loop per-run, loop retry, sequential per-run, sequential per-story).\n193\t- The function guards on `taskName === 'implement'` and `contract?.testResults` being non-null, so it's safe to call unconditionally after every dispatch.\n194\t- Currently the engine builds output contracts with `testResults: null` (hardcoded). Flag propagation will activate when the engine gains test result parsing from agent output (likely a future story). The logic is tested via contract mutation in `writeOutputContract` mock.\n195\t- Added 8 unit tests covering all acceptance criteria.\n196\t- Confirmed `checkPreconditions()` in `src/modules/verify/orchestrator.ts` already reads the exact flags set by this feature — no changes needed.\n197\t- All 4747 tests pass with zero regressions.\n198\t\n199\t### File List\n200\t\n201\t- `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — added import for `readStateWithBody`/`writeState`, added `propagateVerifyFlags()` function, inserted calls at all dispatch sites\n202\t- `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts` — added mocks for `state.js`, added 8 tests for flag propagation\n203\t- `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-4-verify-flag-propagation.md` — updated status to review, marked tasks complete\n204\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01RPX2BVG1Wh216aTDGfS7Tq","session_id":"9476bbd2-ee0a-4a5e-ac2a-0ed5228c47bf","uuid":"52aae99f-cecd-41bd-afc9-8e23838caf46","timesta